<i>noun</i>: 수행 [수행], 금욕주의 [그ː묙쭈의/그ː묙쭈이], 고행 [고행] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>수행 [수행]</dt><br>
<dd>1. asceticism</dd><br>
<dd>몸과 마음을 바르게 갈고 닦음.</dd><br>
<dd>The cultivation of one's body and mind in the right manner.</dd><br>
<dd>2. Buddhist asceticism</dd><br>
<dd>불교에서, 부처의 가르침을 실천하고 도를 닦음.</dd><br>
<dd>In Buddhism, the act of practicing the teachings of Buddha and cultivating oneself for religious reasons.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>금욕주의 [그ː묙쭈의/그ː묙쭈이]</dt><br>
<dd>stoicism; asceticism</dd><br>
<dd>몸과 마음의 욕구나 욕망을 억제하여 이상을 성취하려는 사상.</dd><br>
<dd>An ideology which achieves its ideals by suppressing the desires and wants of the mind and body.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>고행 [고행]</dt><br>
<dd>1. penance; asceticism; mortification</dd><br>
<dd>불교에서, 몸으로 견디기 어려운 일들을 통하여 수행을 쌓는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>In Buddhism, an act of making oneself suffer physically, with an intention to suppress one's desire and find illumination.</dd><br>
<dd>2. suffering</dd><br>
<dd>(비유적으로) 힘들고 괴로운 일을 겪음.</dd><br>
<dd>(figurative) An act of going through a difficult and agonizing incident.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>